Module 1: Ambitions, Dreams, and the Road to 100 Iterations
The Purpose of This Recording
I am using "Talk Tanglish" and my personal mobile recorder to capture these briefs as a personal reminder. It serves as a way to document my thoughts and track my progress as I move forward.

The Vision: Teaching Through Visualization
In this module, I want to talk about my ambition and my dream. It’s quite simple: I want to be a teacher who explains the most complex subjects in the easiest way possible. My inspiration comes from a great physics teacher I had. He had a unique style—he would draw everything he taught. He gave me a piece of advice that stuck:

"Whatever it is you are teaching, and whoever you are teaching it to, if you can draw it out, you will reach them much more easily."

Through him, I didn't just learn physics; I learned the art of how to learn and how to communicate effectively.

The Philosophy: Connecting the Dots
I know that I want to be a teacher, but as Steve Jobs famously said, "You can't connect the dots looking forward; you can only connect them looking backwards." I don't have a perfect vision of exactly how the future will unfold, but I have a very clear idea of what I need to do in the present.

The Roadmap: Academics and Technical Mastery
My immediate focus is on my academics—I need to crack those first. Parallel to that, I am already proficient in web coding. However, I want to expand my horizons further:

Coding Fundamentals: Strengthening the core.

Data Science & AI: Diving deep into Kaggle and Deep Learning frameworks.

The "100 Iterations" Framework
I’ve set a goal for myself: I want to complete 100 iterations. To me, an iteration is a new project, a new learning milestone, or a different challenge. Once I cross that 100th iteration, I plan to:

Significantly develop my skills.

Optimize my LinkedIn and GitHub profiles.

Secure a high-quality internship at a great company.

Closing Thoughts
This is the first module, the first iteration. By the time I reach my 100th module, I will document exactly where I am. I’m aiming for that dream internship and a solid career start. Let’s see how it unfolds.
